    "context": "Most Hong Kongers live in high-rise apartments and share a lift with dozens of neighbours. Lift encounters are short and friendly, just enough to be neighbourly without overstaying your welcome. A smile and basic pleasantries go a long way.",
    "cultural_note": "In many Hong Kong buildings, the lift buttons skip the number 4, jumping from 3 to 5, because 四 (sei3, four) sounds like 死 (sei2, death). Buildings also omit 14, 24, 34, and any floor ending in 4, replacing them with 3A, 13A, and so on. Some towers also remove 13 for Western reasons. The result is a 50-floor building where no one can quite agree what floor they live on.",
